The paper deals with the Feedback Vertex Set problem and its subset versions in directed graphs, which are classic problems in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. The techniques used in the paper involve random sampling and important separators, which are commonly used in algorithm design and analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
